
[1]toughness

   TOUGHNESS, n. tuf'ness. The quality of a substance which renders it in
   some degree flexible, without brittleness or liability to fracture;
   flexibility with a firm adhesion of parts; as the toughness of steel.

   1. Viscosity; tenacity; clamminess; glutinousness; as the toughness of
   mucus.

   2. Firmness; strength of constitution or texture.
